featured_reviews.review_id:
This mosque is centrally located in Alinagar colony with 40 feet road around all sides of mosque. Currently the salat area is built within 20% of area and is built in two parts:
1. Main sehan which gated and has 10 rows for prayer.
2. Verandah seham which is open and has 7 rows. In the east south side it houses ablution area (wuzu khana) and restrooms & bathing area.

Currently the structure is only on ground floor but for Friday prayer arrangement on the roof is also made. In terms of capacity mosque can house 5000 namazis at a time.

The masjid also has Deen Lectures orated by Imam Sb. after the salat of Asr. During prayer there are oy 2-3 rows of namazis and during Juma salat it has more than 3k namazis.

The masjid total area spans around 50k sqft. approx. but the actual uses as of now is only 20%.

featured_reviews.review_id:
One of the most old masjid in patna
As you know, in all Muslim countries Azan is called aloud five times a day and you must have heard it. Have you ever wondered how it started?

STORY OF AZAN

A long time ago when the Muslims migrated from Mecca to Madinah they used to agree about a fixed time for the congregational prayer. They found it difficult to remember the time fixed for the prayer sometimes, especially when they were busy doing their work. One day Prophet Muhammad(saw) and the Muslims discussed the matter of calling the people for the congregational prayer at the exact time. Some of the believers suggested the use of something like the bell of the Christians, others suggested the use of a horn like that of the Jews, but Umar(ra) suggested sending someone to announce the prayer. Then Allah's Messenger(saw) appointed Bilal(ra) to call the people to prayer. But it seems through the study of hadith that the method was not satisfactory. Then Prophet Muhammad(saw) agreed to use a Naqoose (a conch), something like the bell of Christians but he was not happy to use it because of its similarity with the Christians.

featured_reviews.review_id: Masjid ghat is situated on the bank of Ganga River in Patna,Bihar, India.It covers approximately 25 metres length. Marks the beginning of the erstwhile riverside Tekari Complex, which stretches Pathri Ghat and beyond in the form of old stony revetments of dilapidated rounded bastions and towers. The Shiva Temple of the erstwhile Tekari Estate exists in the eastern end of Raushan Ghat. The temple was erected by Maharaja Mitrajit Singh of Tekari in early 19th century. Raja Mitrajit Singh purchased the property and gifted to his second son. The Ghat is connected with the Ashok Rajpath (through the 'North-South Tekari Road'), where lies the Patthar-Ki-Masjid built during the rule of Jahangir (1620s). Further south of Masjid, the DARGAH OF SHAH ARZANI.

Also known as High court Dargaah ki masjid is a huge mosque adjacent to the Patna High Court situated on Bailey Road 250 Mts from Income Tax Round About and 1.2 KMs from Patna Railway Station. The mosque has an accommodation capacity of more than 1000 people.
The most beautiful thing is that the mosque has attachment with great Waliullah "Sheed Syed Gulam Safdar Peer Murad Shah rahmatullah Alaih" where devotees from across the State comes to offer their Chadar and to gain spirituality.
Muballigs of Dawate Islami , a global non political , non profit Islamic organisation gives Dars e Faizane Sunnat after Zohar namaz daily. Alhaj Allama Maulana Alhafiz Azmatullah Rahmani Sahab is the Imam of mosque since 1996.
